-- Spain Defeats Ireland 4-0 in Group C at European Championship
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-06-14T20:35:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/spain-defeats-ireland-4-0-in-group-c-at-european-championship.html
Spain defeated Ireland 4-0 to tie
Croatia at the top of Group C at the European soccer
championship.  Fernando Torres scored two goals and  David Silva  and Cesc
Fabregas had one each for the defending champion in Gdansk,
Poland.    Spain had four points from two games to match Croatia,
which rallied to tie Italy 1-1. Italy has two points and
Ireland, which was eliminated with the loss, has none.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  